; node-exchange.form - offered/requested/delivered nodes.
;
; THE ASK
;   Nodes can be offered and requested and delivered with consent or following
;   any shared interface.
;
; THE SHAPE
;   A node is a content-addressed thing with a kind, privacy band, size, layer,
;   and receipt. A cell or organ can offer that node. Another can request it.
;   Delivery happens when the request fits the offer and either:
;     - explicit consent is present, or
;     - the request action is honored by the offered shared interface.
;
;   A shared interface is already a consent membrane. It is not a loophole.
;
; RUNNABLE HEART
;   form-stdlib/node-exchange.fk names:
;     nx-node              NodeID, kind, privacy, bytes, layer, receipt
;     nx-offer             offerer, node, offered interface, consent, bounds
;     nx-request           requester, kind, action, receiver interface, bounds
;     nx-consentful?       explicit consent OR honored shared interface
;     nx-deliverable?      offer + request + channel + bounds + consent/interface
;     nx-deliver           delivered/withheld receipt row
;
; DELIVERY CONDITIONS
;   A node delivery requires:
;     - non-empty NodeID
;     - node receipt
;     - offer receipt
;     - request receipt
;     - kind match
;     - privacy within both offer and request bounds
;     - size within both offer and request bounds
;     - explicit consent or request action honored by offered interface
;     - open, connected Hati channel with enough bandwidth
;
; INTERFACE EXAMPLE
;   An organ may offer `(m-offer, m-witness)` for a temperature summary node.
;   A requester asking with `m-offer` can receive it through that shared
;   interface. A requester asking with a mode outside the offered interface is
;   answered with `withheld`, with receipt.
;
; HOW IT LAYERS
;   node-exchange composes with cell-organ-layer:
;     cells form organs
;     organs open channels
;     substrate layers carry address/consent/receipt
;     nodes are offered/requested/delivered through those channels
;     delivered nodes can promote through summary -> memory -> prediction ->
;     report -> research only while receipts and consent remain intact.
;
; PROOF
;   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk \
;     form-stdlib/channel-interface.fk \
;     form-stdlib/hati-mesh.fk \
;     form-stdlib/cell-organ-layer.fk \
;     form-stdlib/node-exchange.fk \
;     form-stdlib/tests/node-exchange-band.fk
;
; KIN
;   cell-organ-layer.form, channel-interface-consent.form, organ-offer.form,
;   hati-mesh.form, mesh-seed.form, organism-mesh.form, mesh-cell-design.form,
;   shared-sensing.form.
